<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  JoeScreen macOS — App Store (TestFlight) entitlements.

  Used by the ship scripts for a TestFlight/App Store distribution build. Deliberately MINIMAL: no
  SharePlay (com.apple.developer.group-session) yet, because that managed capability needs Apple
  approval and an unapproved restricted entitlement breaks automatic signing (same rule as iOS). Once
  group-session is approved for com.joescreen.app, add it here.

  App Sandbox is DELIBERATELY omitted (D6): CGEvent input injection needs kTCCServicePostEvent /
  Accessibility, unavailable to sandboxed apps — this is why the app ships via TestFlight/Developer-ID,
  NOT the Mac App Store. TestFlight accepts a non-sandboxed app; it only needs the App Store
  provisioning profile (which the com.apple.application-identifier the profile injects satisfies).

  Hardened Runtime (ENABLE_HARDENED_RUNTIME=YES) is on for notarization. Under hardened runtime the
  mic/camera are BLOCKED at the runtime layer — before TCC even prompts — unless these device
  entitlements are present. They are NOT managed/restricted (no Apple approval needed), so they don't
  break automatic signing. Without them a Release/notarized build can't enable voice or the webcam
  (the toggle silently no-ops; no permission prompt ever appears). See RISKS / the mic-camera fix.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.device.camera</key>
	<true/>
</dict>
</plist>
